Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.67,0:00:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My king.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.59,0:00:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,General.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.21,0:00:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve starved them out,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.76,0:00:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehoiachin still refuses to meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.34,0:00:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Negotiations don’t concern me, General,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.72,0:00:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but your incompetence does.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.18,0:00:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Finish it,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.85,0:00:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,or you’ll not find me as forgiving as the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.10,0:00:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, my king.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.54,0:01:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what Jehovah of armies says,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.87,0:01:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Because you did not obey my words,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.25,0:01:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,‘all this land will be reduced to ruins,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.13,0:01:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and this land and its inhabitants
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.13,0:01:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,‘will have to serve the king of Babylon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.30,0:01:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,for 70 years.’
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.69,0:01:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.90,0:01:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.44,0:01:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s almost sundown!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.73,0:01:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Jeremiah was speaking today, and I, uh
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.15,0:01:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,—I stopped by the temple on the way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.91,0:01:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we’re almost ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.96,0:01:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You were at the temple again today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.97,0:01:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.13,0:01:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“To gaze upon the pleasantness of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.51,0:01:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and to look with appreciation upon his temple.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.48,0:02:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I have something for you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.36,0:02:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can always have Jehovah’s words with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.66,0:02:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.09,0:02:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.13,0:02:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s going to happen to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.84,0:02:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What always happens to Jehovah’s faithful servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.10,0:02:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Have no fear, Jehovah is our shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.73,0:02:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Dinner’s ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.66,0:03:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see our old neighbor at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.75,0:03:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn’t see him at all today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.38,0:03:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of strange,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.38,0:03:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw our neighbor Eli the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.38,0:03:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Eli is always getting into trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.97,0:03:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.97,0:03:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Son, pick a psalm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.48,0:03:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah is my light and my salvation.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.10,0:03:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You always choose that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.07,0:03:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hushim.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.15,0:03:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah is my light
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.36,0:03:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“and my salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.24,0:03:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Whom should I fear?”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.54,0:04:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.91,0:04:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay and play?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.79,0:04:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve got to go with Papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.79,0:04:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,When you come back, do you want to play Noah’s ark?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.80,0:04:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.67,0:04:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And who will you be?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.17,0:04:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll be a lion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.55,0:04:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.26,0:04:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I’ll be an elephant.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.86,0:04:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehoiachin has surrendered!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.90,0:05:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehoiachin has surrendered!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.95,0:05:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Household of Eber, tribe of Judah,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.03,0:05:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,open up at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.58,0:05:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,All of you outside! Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.20,0:05:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s happened. They’re here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.20,0:05:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Gather your things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.75,0:05:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.79,0:05:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.67,0:05:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.25,0:05:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t live here anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.14,0:05:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hushim, grab our bags.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.41,0:07:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate this place!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.29,0:07:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.32,0:07:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Open up! 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.66,0:07:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,All four—outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.29,0:07:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Check the back room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.42,0:08:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,By the order of the king, you are coming with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.13,0:08:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel, of the tribe of Judah—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.18,0:08:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You will receive training
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.18,0:08:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in the house of the great King Nebuchadnezzar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.52,0:08:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.81,0:08:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Princes and nobles belong in the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.03,0:08:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s not a prince; he’s just a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.37,0:08:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.33,0:08:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, I will go if it’s a servant you seek.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.79,0:08:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No! I’m taking the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.62,0:08:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.50,0:08:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.83,0:08:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we say goodbye?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.72,0:08:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Make it quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.07,0:09:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Be strong, my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.32,0:09:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.84,0:10:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.31,0:10:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Mishael.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.27,0:10:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you seen anyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.48,0:10:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn’t think we’d let you come here alone, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.48,0:10:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Azariah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.44,0:10:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hananiah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.69,0:10:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Chislon and Ahitub.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.44,0:10:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.44,0:10:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Move along.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.62,0:10:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.58,0:10:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The palace, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.41,0:10:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So like Joseph in Pharaoh’s house?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.41,0:10:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No, like Joseph in the dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.75,0:10:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn’t seem so bad to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.46,0:10:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.76,0:10:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Chislon, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.80,0:10:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don’t say something, I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.97,0:10:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.97,0:10:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.01,0:11:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.22,0:11:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back again sometime.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.33,0:11:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the Jewish boys that Ashpenaz summoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.88,0:12:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You have been chosen
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.88,0:12:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because you are wise,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.13,0:12:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but you are lacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.68,0:12:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You will learn our writing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.89,0:12:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and our language.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.40,0:12:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be given new names,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.78,0:12:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and at the end of three years,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.99,0:12:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you will serve the great King Nebuchadnezzar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.95,0:12:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Today,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.96,0:12:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you are foreigners
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.09,0:12:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,—tomorrow, the gods willing,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.26,0:13:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Babylonians.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.63,0:13:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Meshach.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.76,0:13:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like a Meshach.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.81,0:13:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Our new names sound like their gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.02,0:13:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,New names, new language—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.73,0:13:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon they’ll want us to worship their gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.73,0:13:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.73,0:14:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,My father had idols, and he worshipped Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.70,0:14:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see the same city I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.36,0:14:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the center of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.99,0:14:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll even eat from the king’s table.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.54,0:14:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What do Babylonians eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.38,0:14:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,His servants are given only the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.14,0:14:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t eat from this food.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.64,0:14:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you making a big deal out of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.73,0:14:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it’s unclean.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.15,0:14:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.11,0:14:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Our, uh, our God
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.41,0:14:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn’t allow us to eat such foods.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.66,0:14:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You fear your God?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.25,0:14:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.83,0:15:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I am afraid of my lord the king,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.30,0:15:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,who has assigned your food and drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.30,0:15:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He insists on these selections
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.47,0:15:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to maintain your strength and vitality.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.60,0:15:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What if he should see you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.44,0:15:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,looking worse in appearance
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.32,0:15:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,than the other youths?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.36,0:15:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You would make me guilty before the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.78,0:15:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I must obey the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.04,0:15:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So must you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.50,0:15:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,—all of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.17,0:15:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When dinner is served, I expect you to be hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.20,0:16:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t speak for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.62,0:16:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.33,0:16:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You can make your own choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.37,0:16:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn’t you hear him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.58,0:16:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.46,0:16:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a new land with new laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.80,0:16:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So what if some of the food is unbled?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.47,0:16:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just food!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.85,0:16:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah commanded us not to eat blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.76,0:16:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s your interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.52,0:16:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“You must not eat . . . any blood at all.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.44,0:16:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s to interpret in that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.56,0:16:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should all take a moment and pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.11,0:16:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.07,0:16:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.95,0:16:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.20,0:16:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is in Israel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.87,0:16:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re in Babylon now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.29,0:16:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you believe that Jehovah is here too?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.75,0:17:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah said that we’re his witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.84,0:17:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What will people say about Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.01,0:17:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,if we give in and break his laws?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.09,0:17:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Your meal is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.37,0:17:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.79,0:17:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.25,0:17:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we eat those foods, we’ll disobey our God.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.84,0:17:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to starve?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.80,0:17:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No, of course not,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.80,0:17:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but He forbids us from eating blood
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.47,0:17:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and food that he calls “unclean.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.97,0:18:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, test your servants for ten days,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.35,0:18:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and let us be given some vegetables to eat
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.56,0:18:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and water to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.61,0:18:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Vegetables?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.28,0:18:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Just give us ten days.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.78,0:18:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And then deal with your servants
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.87,0:18:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,according to what you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.97,0:18:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten days.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.48,0:18:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go, thanks to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.87,0:19:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to try this meat. It’s amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.34,0:19:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you seen anything like this before?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.85,0:20:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Really!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.85,0:20:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Oh, wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.31,0:20:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.45,0:21:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Ashpenaz has summoned you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.93,0:21:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, these young men are of royal . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.30,0:21:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I know who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.61,0:21:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve been watching you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.49,0:21:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,—all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.16,0:21:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t bow to our idols,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.67,0:21:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you pray only to your God,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.88,0:22:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and you are not eating our foods.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.47,0:22:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They insisted that their God would not . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.68,0:22:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.22,0:22:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you look healthier than the others. 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.35,0:22:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Continue giving them the diet they’ve requested.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.23,0:22:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And Belteshazzar,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.37,0:22:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,your future is bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.37,0:22:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t waste it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.31,0:22:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring in the next group.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.91,0:23:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The total rations would be fifteen {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}kurru,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.53,0:23:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,two {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}p{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}ān{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}u,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.99,0:23:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and five {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}s{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}ūtu.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.00,0:23:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.54,0:23:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,How much interest
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.55,0:23:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,may a merchant charge on money and grain?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.14,0:23:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be 40 percent, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.68,0:23:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty percent?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you learned only to be a thief
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.18,0:23:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the past three years?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.94,0:23:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And you, Meshach?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.02,0:23:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate is 20 percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.69,0:23:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.86,0:23:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Which star of Enlil is brightest
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.12,0:23:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Urgula constellation?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.26,0:24:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.55,0:24:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the Lugal star.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.93,0:24:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.64,0:24:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a tower that is high
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.76,0:24:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but, nonetheless, has no shade.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.81,0:24:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.73,0:24:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Your ziggurat?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.78,0:24:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.58,0:24:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You can solve the riddle?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.29,0:24:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It is sunlight, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.08,0:24:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.17,0:24:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,My wise men teach that the gods
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.92,0:24:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,are responsible for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.05,0:24:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If that’s so,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.05,0:24:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,why do the good suffer and the evil prosper?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.26,0:24:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No one has been able to answer . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.27,0:25:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,As you say, O king,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.28,0:25:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,‘the wise do not always have the food,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.32,0:25:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,‘nor do the intelligent always have the riches,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.82,0:25:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,‘nor do those with knowledge always have success,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.45,0:25:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,‘because time and unexpected events
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.83,0:25:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,overtake them all.’
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.96,0:25:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Who wrote those words?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.59,0:25:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.51,0:25:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Famed for his wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.26,0:25:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But its source was his God,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.18,0:25:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,our God, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.77,0:25:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Take them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.27,0:25:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When should we return?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.86,0:25:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You won’t!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.32,0:25:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back to your families.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.28,0:25:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve proven worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.20,0:26:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Belteshazzar, no—not the four of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.50,0:26:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We have more to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.22,0:26:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not know your God,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.22,0:26:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but you’ve proven to be ten times better
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.39,0:26:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,than any priest or conjurer that I’ve met.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.69,0:26:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ashpenaz will arrange
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.27,0:26:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,for you to serve in the palace with my wise men.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.27,0:26:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe your gifts were wasted in Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.28,0:26:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but here they will be put to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.42,0:26:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The victory in Jerusalem is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.10,0:27:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Our forces are now preparing to besiege Tyre.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.27,0:27:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They should remember what happened to Zedekiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.98,0:27:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The gods are with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.54,0:27:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerah,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.79,0:27:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.46,0:27:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s about Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.28,0:27:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.90,0:27:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To see my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.51,0:28:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This year, we’ve had to make do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.15,0:28:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.76,0:29:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.39,0:29:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.48,0:29:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.70,0:29:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They tore down the walls;
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.07,0:29:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,they torched its towers.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.67,0:29:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Many died.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.30,0:29:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And they burned down Jehovah’s house!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.30,0:29:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn’t our people listen?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.18,0:29:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they think Jehovah couldn’t see
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.98,0:29:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what they were doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.61,0:29:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as our temple existed,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.61,0:30:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,our people had hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.16,0:30:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as Jehovah exists,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.24,0:30:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we have hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.87,0:30:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But he’s rejected us
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.96,0:30:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because of our unrighteousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.38,0:30:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He hasn’t
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.59,0:30:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,—not everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.76,0:30:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah told Ezekiel
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.55,0:30:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that in his eyes you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.06,0:30:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,are as righteous as Noah
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.98,0:30:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and Job.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.90,0:30:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.78,0:30:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He did.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.37,0:30:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If Jehovah cares so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.58,0:30:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,then why are we in exile? 
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.47,0:31:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can’t we go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.72,0:31:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can’t we be together?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.01,0:31:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You are home, Son.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.12,0:31:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t have all the answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.75,0:31:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay close to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.38,0:31:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be blessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.06,0:32:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Call the wise men!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.94,0:32:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.65,0:32:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’m agitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.07,0:32:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to know what I dreamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.07,0:32:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,O king, may you live on forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.07,0:32:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Relate the dream to your servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.41,0:32:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We will tell the interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.95,0:32:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.33,0:32:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don’t make the dream known to me
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.95,0:32:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,along with the interpretation,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.95,0:32:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll be dismembered,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.58,0:33:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and your houses will be turned into public latrines.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.67,0:33:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you do, tell me the dream
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.63,0:33:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and the interpretation,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.63,0:33:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you will receive gifts and a reward
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.18,0:33:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and great honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.26,0:33:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve got to buy some time
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.39,0:33:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can consult the spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.47,0:33:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The scrolls will tell you what the dreams say.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.48,0:33:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to come up with a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.19,0:33:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants us to tell him the dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.44,0:33:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.44,0:33:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No one has ever asked this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.61,0:33:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.61,0:33:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.61,0:33:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can buy us some time,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.78,0:33:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we can consult the spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.86,0:33:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve agreed to tell me something false
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.12,0:33:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and deceitful until the situation changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.24,0:33:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Deceitful?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.70,0:33:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Deceitful!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.67,0:33:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There is not a man on earth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.67,0:33:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,who can do what the king demands.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.75,0:33:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What the king is asking is difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.46,0:33:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No one exists who could tell this to the king except
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.05,0:33:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,—except the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.15,0:34:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Arioch,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.11,0:34:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,seize them!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.11,0:34:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Down!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.74,0:34:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Down!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.19,0:34:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill them!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.61,0:34:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Call the wise men!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.78,0:34:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.87,0:34:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Go, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.33,0:34:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,By the order of the king, round them up!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.21,0:34:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.21,0:34:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.29,0:34:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.17,0:34:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t hear everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.00,0:34:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but the wise men angered the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.75,0:34:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is to be executed by dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.42,0:34:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.26,0:34:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll try to learn more.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.35,0:34:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes—Chaldean, Egyptian, Jewish
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.89,0:34:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,—all the wise men.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.15,0:34:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Arioch?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.40,0:34:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Belteshazzar, you shouldn’t be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.74,0:34:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is there such a harsh order from the king?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.32,0:34:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.37,0:34:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and no one can tell him what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.37,0:35:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Flee now!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.37,0:35:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you escape before dawn, you might survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.59,0:35:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me why I asked for them
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.14,0:35:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and you haven’t brought them?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.14,0:35:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Why aren’t the gods talking to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.56,0:35:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I want them and all of their families brought here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.86,0:35:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to look into the whites of their eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.11,0:35:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask them why.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.25,0:35:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang them without their skins!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.46,0:35:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the gods look down on their flesh,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.80,0:35:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and then throw their bodies in the Euphrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.17,0:35:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ashpenaz.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.22,0:36:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What good are wise men without wisdom?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.26,0:36:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.81,0:36:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to speak with the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.14,0:36:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.73,0:36:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, let me speak with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.48,0:36:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, this is Belteshazzar.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.53,0:36:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,O king,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.20,0:36:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,interpretations belong to my God, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.37,0:36:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows your dream and what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.33,0:36:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, where is your God? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.13,0:36:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe that he—
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.63,0:36:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that he will reveal it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.80,0:36:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, give me time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.48,0:36:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We have until morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.94,0:36:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,To do what?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.06,0:36:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To reveal the dream to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.57,0:36:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how much of the dream
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.99,0:37:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,has Jehovah revealed to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.87,0:37:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, nothing yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.66,0:37:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah revealed
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.21,0:37:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that he would interpret it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.79,0:37:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Not exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.34,0:37:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.34,0:37:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you know this is even going to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.84,0:37:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I can’t be sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.89,0:37:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You’d better be sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.35,0:37:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.43,0:37:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If he reveals the dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.77,0:37:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,it proves that he’s the true God!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.94,0:37:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.95,0:37:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.95,0:37:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.00,0:37:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray that Jehovah have mercy on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.38,0:38:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.59,0:38:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,surely you didn’t bring us here just to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.35,0:38:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What will people say?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.48,0:38:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We told them that you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.48,0:38:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,are the God of the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.07,0:38:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the only God who can reveal secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.28,0:38:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Please,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.07,0:38:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,vindicate yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.78,0:39:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerah!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.01,0:39:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I have found a man from the exiles of Judah
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.51,0:39:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who can make known the interpretation to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.23,0:39:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I know who he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.44,0:39:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you really make known to me
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.40,0:39:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the dream that I saw
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.73,0:39:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and its interpretation?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.66,0:39:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a God in the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.67,0:39:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,who is a Revealer of secrets,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.50,0:40:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and he has made known to King Nebuchadnezzar
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.34,0:40:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,what is to happen in the final part of the days.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.39,0:40:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your dream:
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.74,0:40:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw an immense image.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.63,0:40:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That image was standing in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.55,0:40:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You yourself are the head of gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.35,0:40:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But after you another kingdom will rise,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.39,0:40:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,inferior to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.77,0:41:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Then another kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.02,0:41:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a third one, of copper,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.40,0:41:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that will rule over the whole earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.48,0:41:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As for the fourth kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.07,0:41:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,it will be strong like iron.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.20,0:41:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The kingdom will be divided.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.83,0:41:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the toes of the feet
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.00,0:41:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,were partly of iron and partly of clay,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.37,0:41:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,so the kingdom will be partly strong
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.67,0:41:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and partly fragile.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.13,0:41:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In the days of those kings,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.13,0:41:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the God of heaven
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.13,0:41:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,will set up a kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.59,0:41:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that will never be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.60,0:41:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And this kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.60,0:41:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,will not be passed on to any other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.15,0:41:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It will crush and put an end
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.16,0:41:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to all these kingdoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.48,0:42:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And it alone will stand forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.16,0:42:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The dream is true,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.46,0:42:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and its interpretation is trustworthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.08,0:43:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.58,0:43:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring a fine robe
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.29,0:43:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and a necklace of gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.30,0:43:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Burn incense before him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.15,0:43:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly your God is a God of gods
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.36,0:44:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and a Lord of kings
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.41,0:44:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and a Revealer of secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.12,0:44:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,May your God be honored
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.12,0:44:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,by the honor I give you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.38,0:44:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You are now ruler over all the province of Babylon.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.88,0:44:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,O king, these servants
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.30,0:44:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,also worship the God in the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.06,0:44:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,May they too be appointed to administer the province?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.31,0:44:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Make the necessary arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.28,0:44:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You have proven far superior
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.28,0:44:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,than these so-called wise men.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.87,0:44:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I now appoint you their chief prefect.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.34,0:44:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear Nebuchadnezzar?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.34,0:45:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When he said, “Your God is a God of gods
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.76,0:45:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and a Lord of kings.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.30,0:45:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah answered your prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.06,0:45:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah answered our prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.37,0:45:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s going to happen next?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.58,0:45:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we go back to Jerusalem?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.67,0:45:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know what happens next,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.67,0:45:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but as long as we stay close to Jehovah . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.63,0:45:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He will always be with us
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.63,0:45:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as we have faith in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.02,0:45:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s nothing in the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.06,0:45:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,about kingdoms crushing kingdoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.06,0:45:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.19,0:46:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.86,0:46:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But how did he know the dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.91,0:46:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Amar-Utu!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.87,0:46:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Amar-Utu, what message from the gods?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.20,0:46:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I have examined a sheep’s liver.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.75,0:46:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Your future is bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.29,0:46:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The stars of Shabatu, the giant,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.96,0:46:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,speak only of your grandeur.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.29,0:46:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m the head of gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.30,0:46:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah said so.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.67,0:46:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Your dream revealed many good things.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.59,0:46:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But this Belteshazzar, he’s a Jew—
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.05,0:46:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s a clever Jew, to be sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.06,0:46:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but he couldn’t interpret dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.06,0:46:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,before he came to Babylon.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.64,0:46:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He first had to be educated here
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.27,0:46:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and given a Babylonian name,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.15,0:46:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a name that honors our great god Bel.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.07,0:46:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Bel used this young captive
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.07,0:46:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to reveal great things to you—
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.70,0:46:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Bel,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.12,0:46:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,not Jehovah, who you defeated in Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.69,0:47:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So the tree is my enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.90,0:47:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it after the seven times pass over?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.82,0:47:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it is you again, O great king.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.12,0:47:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You are fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.75,0:47:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,At last—
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.84,0:47:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Belteshazzar, chief of the magic-practicing priests,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.76,0:47:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,all of the other wise men are unable
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.09,0:47:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to make the interpretation known to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.68,0:47:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But you are able to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.06,0:48:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Explain to me the visions I’ve seen in my dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.49,0:48:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.45,0:48:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw a tree in the midst of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.96,0:48:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and its height, it was enormous
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.38,0:48:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,—it was enormous.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.67,0:48:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the tree grew and became strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.30,0:48:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and its top—
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.30,0:48:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And its top reached the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.93,0:48:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,reached the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.14,0:48:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and the tree grew and became strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.27,0:48:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . holy one . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.31,0:48:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Chop down the tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.10,0:48:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw a watcher . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.27,0:48:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Chop down the tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.85,0:48:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . with a banding of iron
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.56,0:48:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and of copper.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.41,0:48:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So who’s the tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.64,0:49:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,O my lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.94,0:49:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,may the dream apply to those hating you
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.10,0:49:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and its interpretation to your enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.82,0:49:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The tree that you saw
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.94,0:49:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that grew great and became strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.07,0:49:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,whose top reached the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.95,0:49:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and was visible to all the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.49,0:49:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,which had beautiful foliage, abundant fruit,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.45,0:49:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and food for all,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.75,0:49:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,beneath which the beasts of the field would dwell
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.08,0:49:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and on whose branches
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.09,0:49:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the birds of the heavens would reside,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.51,0:49:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it is you, O king.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.64,0:49:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And the king saw a watcher, a holy one,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.68,0:49:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,coming down from the heavens who was saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.85,0:50:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“Chop down the tree and destroy it,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.37,0:50:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“but leave the stump with its roots in the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.42,0:50:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“with a banding of iron and of copper.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.59,0:50:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“And let the dew of the heavens make it wet,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.84,0:50:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“and let its portion be
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.84,0:50:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“with the beasts of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.68,0:50:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,until seven times pass over it.”
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.56,0:50:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the interpretation, O king;
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.56,0:50:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it is the decree of the Most High.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.77,0:50:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be driven away from among men,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.90,0:50:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and your dwelling will be with the beasts of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.91,0:50:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will be given vegetation to eat
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.49,0:50:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,just like bulls,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.16,0:51:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will become wet
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.87,0:51:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with the dew of the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.04,0:51:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and seven times will pass over you
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.25,0:51:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,until you know
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.34,0:51:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Most High is Ruler
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.38,0:51:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in the kingdom of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.46,0:51:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he grants it to whomever he wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.18,0:51:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But because they said to leave
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.18,0:51:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the stump of the tree with its roots,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.43,0:51:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,your kingdom will be yours again
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.60,0:51:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,after you come to know
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.77,0:51:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that the heavens are ruling.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.36,0:51:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn away from your sins
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.74,0:51:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,by doing what is right
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.86,0:51:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and from your iniquity
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.16,0:51:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,by showing mercy to the poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.49,0:51:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It may be that your prosperity will be extended.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.64,0:51:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Does Belteshazzar know when this will happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.30,0:52:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.85,0:52:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But your wise men
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.85,0:52:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,doubt that his interpretation can be trusted.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.69,0:52:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the facts:
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.32,0:52:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Egypt’s gods told the Egyptians
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.32,0:52:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that they would defeat us.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.20,0:52:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, you destroyed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.95,0:52:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So why should the God of the Jews
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.62,0:52:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,be given any more credit?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.21,0:52:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at what you’ve done.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.09,0:52:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The gods are with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.89,0:52:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You have made Babylon
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.01,0:52:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the greatest kingdom on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.98,0:52:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Belteshazzar wants you to grovel like a slave
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.90,0:52:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.98,0:52:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A strong king means a strong kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.32,0:53:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us continue with our discussion
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.57,0:53:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of the stars of Enlil.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.12,0:53:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the Lugal star is the brightest star
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.83,0:53:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Urgula constellation.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.50,0:53:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The stars are reliable,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.00,0:53:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,unlike the gods of defeated nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.13,0:53:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back to Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.80,0:53:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you could
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.55,0:53:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,if there was anything left of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.52,0:53:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Has Jehovah revealed anything new?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.61,0:53:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been ten months
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.61,0:53:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and still no sign of this supposed insanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.58,0:53:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I trust my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.24,0:53:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, as we do when we read the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.12,0:53:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But we still shape the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.17,0:53:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be held responsible for the words,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.30,0:53:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and when a wise man speaks lies, well . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.05,0:54:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I spoke only what Jehovah revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.35,0:54:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you forgotten what happened
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.27,0:54:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,when some couldn’t interpret the dream image?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.89,0:54:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,A death sentence followed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.73,0:54:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was a flattering interpretation,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.61,0:54:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that the king was a head of gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.40,0:54:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, you’ve said he’ll go mad,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.07,0:54:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.37,0:54:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.58,0:54:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe, maybe not.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.75,0:54:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But your words are against the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.46,0:54:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.29,0:54:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And no one can protect you from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.99,0:55:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten months.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.57,0:55:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.16,0:55:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But your words are against the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.54,0:55:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Still no sign of this supposed insanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.42,0:55:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.63,0:55:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And no one can protect you from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.46,0:56:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can always have Jehovah’s words with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.77,0:56:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“Instruct me in your way, O Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.98,0:56:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not hand me over to my adversaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.06,0:56:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“for false witnesses have risen up against me,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.48,0:56:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“and they threaten me with violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.45,0:56:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“Where would I be if I did not have faith
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.12,0:56:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“that I would see Jehovah’s goodness
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.25,0:56:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in the land of the living?”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.58,0:56:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, test your servants for ten days.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.00,0:56:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, you look healthier than the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.76,0:56:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Continue giving them the diet they’ve requested.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.55,0:56:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not know your God,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.89,0:56:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but you’ve proven
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.01,0:56:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to be ten times better than any priest
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.31,0:56:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,or conjurer I’ve met.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.94,0:57:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.27,0:57:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and no one can tell him what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.53,0:57:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah answered your prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.91,0:57:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“Hope in Jehovah;
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.13,0:57:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“be courageous and strong of heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.25,0:57:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, hope in Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.81,0:57:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare a sacrifice to Bel.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.32,0:57:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,To the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.95,0:57:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,To the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.54,0:58:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This city is the jewel of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.21,0:58:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the Ishtar Gate, the gardens,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.71,0:58:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the ziggurat so high
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.92,0:58:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it reaches the gods themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.21,0:58:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No one would question that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.93,0:58:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s odd that only twelve months ago
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.97,0:58:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,one of your servants
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.01,0:58:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,dared to suggest that you’d go insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.47,0:58:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this not Babylon the Great
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.73,0:58:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that I myself have built for the royal house
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.48,0:58:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,with my own strength and might
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.03,0:58:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and for the glory of my majesty?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.28,0:58:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“To you it is being said,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.82,0:58:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“O King Nebuchadnezzar,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.99,0:58:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘The kingdom has gone away from you,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.24,0:58:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and from mankind you are being driven away.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.66,0:58:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘With the beasts of the field your dwelling will be,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.00,0:58:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and you will be given vegetation
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.00,0:58:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘to eat just like bulls,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.51,0:58:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and seven times will pass over you,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.80,0:58:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘until you know that the Most High
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.47,0:58:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘is Ruler in the kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.56,0:59:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘of mankind and that he grants it
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.73,0:59:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to whomever he wants.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.40,0:59:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Stop! Stop! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.44,0:59:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.61,0:59:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.89,0:59:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When you and your wise men
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.89,0:59:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,have failed consistently,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.68,0:59:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,how can you claim Daniel to be a fraud?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.35,0:59:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.64,0:59:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel conspired against your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.06,0:59:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.65,0:59:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how did he make it happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.95,0:59:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything he has said has come true,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.07,1:00:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which is quite different from our history with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.20,1:00:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My father trusted you,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.20,1:00:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and I trusted you, and you were all wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.54,1:00:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Either you failed or Marduk did.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.54,1:00:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.71,1:00:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me:
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.96,1:00:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this God in the heavens, Jehovah?
